race.comment: AXIUS (2) progressive gelding resuming. Went to a new level when last in work and should get the right conditions to test some of these first-up. Fitted with the one trial and the booking of Nash Rawiller is a good lead. SNACK BAR (4) sat on the good tempo first-up when an unlucky second to Lyles over 1100m at Rosehill. Poorly drawn here but has the class to figure prominently. MISS KIM KAR (10) sharp mare who can sprint well fresh if the rain arrives. Fitted with the two strong trials and will be charging late. SMASHING TIME (11) looks a more consistent type this prep but struggling to draw a decent gate. Pushed forward from the wide barrier when a game third over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Sure to be thereabouts.
